<subSubSection id="3548BB395D21638848EECE79A2CC9AC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DB7C1A45FD587169271EA89CF0566A1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3EF48E449E704B1CBED4E58B5F3E9CF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0352297A108C4D95AC01F3504FA8E7A7" genus="A." lsidName="A. maguanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="maguanensis">
<emphasis id="64A8B879D7B8EB349BA96D9842CEAE24" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">A. maguanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W.H.Chen &amp; Y.M.Shui with three major staminodes and style longer than ovary, but differs in its elliptic bracts (
<emphasis id="2F262A87FEAD573A446D0D385412DC17" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">vs.</emphasis>
broadly ovate to rounded), triangular calyx lobes awny at the apex (
<emphasis id="F7993F15CB4CDF428160062490A91C59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">vs.</emphasis>
elliptic and beaked at the apex), and lateral staminodes with red glands (
<emphasis id="9D6A14A24119AD32F6AE92863F964274" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">vs.</emphasis>
without red glands).
</paragraph>
